[src:symfony/page-creation] You can add the body element yourself, or extend `base.html.twig`, which contains all default HTML elements.
[src:symfony/page-creation] In the templates article, you'll learn all about Twig: how to loop, render other templates and leverage its powerful layout inheritance system.
[src:symfony/page-creation] Most of the time, you'll be working in `src/`, `templates/` or `config/`.
[src:symfony/page-creation] As you keep reading, you'll learn what can be done inside each of these.
